Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.12,0:02:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,原子使所有事情變得有生氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Atoms let matter do funny things.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.66,0:02:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,要瞭解水 你需要知道它的原子規律\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}To understand water, you need to know what its atoms are doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.62,0:02:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,每個水分子都是由\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Every molecule of water is composed
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.16,0:02:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,兩個小小的氫原子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of two tiny hydrogen atoms
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.73,0:02:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,附著在一個大的氧原子上組成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}attached to a larger oxygen atom.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.40,0:03:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,因此我們稱之為 一氧化二氫\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's why we call it H20.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.50,0:03:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,如果溫度不冷不熱\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If it's not too hot or too cold,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.64,0:03:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,分子們可以相互翻滾穿行\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the molecules can slide and tumble past each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.34,0:03:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,分子間還是有一些的粘滯性\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's still some stickiness between the molecules,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.64,0:03:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,但是不足以讓它們變的緊密\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but not enough to lock them into a rigid solid.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.91,0:03:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是液體的特性\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's what makes something a liquid.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.68,0:03:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽將水加熱\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The sun warms the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.35,0:03:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,給它更多的能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And with more energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.75,0:03:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,分子們移動加快\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the molecules move faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.69,0:03:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,溫度就是這樣的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's all that temperature is.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.49,0:03:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,當分子運到快到足以\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Those molecules are moving fast enough
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.49,0:03:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,打破彼此間脆弱的聯繫時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to break the weak bonds that hold them to their neighbors.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.66,0:03:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,就是蒸發\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's evaporation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.56,0:03:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,我們呼吸的空氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The air we breathe is made of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.50,0:03:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,就是由氮和氧的分子組成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}nitrogen and oxygen molecules
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.53,0:03:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,再加一些水蒸氣和二氧化碳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with a scattering of water vapor and carbon dioxide.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.33,0:03:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,小心\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Incoming!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.34,0:03:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,那是冷凝\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's condensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.61,0:03:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,露珠就是冷凝戰勝蒸發的勝利果實\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A dewdrop is the momentary triumph of condensation over evaporation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.34,0:03:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,這種現象持續下去\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And while it lasts,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.11,0:03:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,它就是一個小宇宙 包含它自己的世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it's a little cosmos with its own worlds...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.58,0:03:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,生物 戲劇性的事情\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}creatures, drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.88,0:03:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,為了探索這滴露珠的廣闊領域\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}To explore the far-flung realms of this dewdrop
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.39,0:03:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我們需要一艘船\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we're gonna need a ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.06,0:04:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,配上兩種引擎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}One with twin engines...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.03,0:04:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,科學和想像力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}science and imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.37,0:04:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,那是單細胞的草履蟲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's a single-celled paramecium,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.30,0:04:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,它是在露珠中遊蕩中眾多嫻熟的獵人之一\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}one of a multitude of skilled hunter-warriors that roam the dewdrop.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.74,0:04:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,但是它們同時也是獵物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But they, too, are hunted.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.11,0:04:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,長頸蟲  草履蟲的死敵\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Dileptus. The paramecium's mortal enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.91,0:04:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,草履蟲或許可以幸運的直接擊殺\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The paramecium might get lucky and score a direct hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.72,0:04:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,就算不能\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Even if it doesn't,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.42,0:04:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,齊射攻擊造成的後座力拉開了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the recoil from the barrage will put some distance
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.99,0:04:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,草履蟲與攻擊者之間的距離\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}between the paramecium and its attacker.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.59,0:04:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我還能說些什麼呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What can I say?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.89,0:04:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,那就是露珠內的生活\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's life in the dewdrop.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.74,0:04:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,那個小傢伙是水熊蟲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That little guy is tardigrade,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.28,0:05:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,一種比針尖還小的動物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}an animal smaller than the head of a pin.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.08,0:05:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,可別小看它\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Don't underestimate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.12,0:05:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,水熊蟲在這個星球上的歷史比我們的還長久\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Tardigrades have been living on this planet a lot longer than we have.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.42,0:05:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,他們已存在地球上大約5億年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}About 500 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.66,0:05:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,和我們的數量比例\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For every one of us,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.70,0:05:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,至少是1比10億\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}there's at least a billion of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.93,0:05:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,它們可以在地球上任何地方生存\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They can make a living anywhere on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.27,0:05:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,在最高的寒冷的山峰頂端\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In the frigid peaks of the tallest mountains,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.94,0:05:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,在噴發的火山口裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the cauldrons of erupting volcanoes,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.81,0:05:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,在大洋的底部\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and in the deep ocean vents at the bottom of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.34,0:05:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,水熊蟲是如此的堅強\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Tardigrades are so tough,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.78,0:05:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,它們可以在真空中生存\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they can survive naked in the vacuum of space.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.22,0:05:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,它們經歷了最近五次的大滅絕\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They've survived all five of the most recent mass extinctions on this planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.89,0:05:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,如果外星人認為地球是水熊蟲的世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A visitor from another world could be forgiven
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.19,0:05:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,那是絕對可以原諒的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for thinking of earth as the planet of the tardigrades.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.33,0:05:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,如果還要看這滴露珠的其他地方 最好繼續往前走\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If we're ever gonna get to the bottom of this dewdrop better get a move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.80,0:06:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,每片葉子和苔蘚\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Every leaf and tiny clump of moss
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.97,0:06:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,都有成千上萬的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}has hundreds of thousands
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.98,0:06:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,顯微鏡才能看見的嘴巴 稱為氣孔\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of microscopic mouths called Stomata.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.48,0:06:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,植物通過它們呼吸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Plants breathe through them,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.48,0:06:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,吸入二氧化碳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}taking in carbon dioxide
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.98,0:06:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,呼出我們賴以生存的氧氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and exhaling the oxygen that we need to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.85,0:06:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,地球上可以沒有我們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The plants can survive without us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.19,0:06:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,但是我們還有其他動物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But we and all the other animals...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.42,0:06:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,離開它們就死翹翹了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we'd be toast without them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.59,0:06:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,地球通過陽光獲取食物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The plants make food out of sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.83,0:06:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,我們動物做不到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We animals can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.23,0:06:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,想看它們是怎麼做到的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}To see how they do it,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.20,0:06:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,我們還要潛的更深\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we have to go deeper,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.73,0:06:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,把我們變小大約1千倍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}make ourselves about a thousand times smaller
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.83,0:06:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,才能進入它們的寶庫\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to get into their treasure house,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.60,0:06:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,它們把好東西都藏在裏面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the place where they keep the good stuff...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.37,0:06:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,那就是葉綠素\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the chlorophyll.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.27,0:06:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,它雖然是個分子 可是卻能負責把陽光轉換成能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's the molecule that converts sunlight into energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.75,0:06:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,每個長方形都是一個植物細胞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Every one of those rectangles is a plant cell.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.95,0:06:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,還有那些小綠車 那都是它的能量工廠\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And those tiny green vehicles are its energy factories.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.85,0:06:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我們可以竊取它們的商業機密\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If we could steal their trade secrets,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.46,0:06:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,又能帶來一次嶄新的工業革命\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it would trigger a new industrial revolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.03,0:06:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,但是要偷窺它們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But to spy on them,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.86,0:06:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,我們還得潛得更深\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we're gonna need to go deeper still.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.55,0:07:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,想像之舟這次又要將我們帶去哪個截然不同的世界呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What alien world has the ship of the imagination carried us to this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.49,0:07:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,它是個宇宙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's the cosmos...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.72,0:07:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,在露珠裏面的宇宙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Contained within a dewdrop.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.39,0:07:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,我們現在做的就是工業間諜活動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We're on an industrial espionage mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.36,0:07:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,如果想刺探葉綠體的商業機密\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If we can penetrate the trade secrets
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.83,0:07:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,葉綠體裏的製作過程\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the manufacturing process in that chloroplast,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.73,0:07:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,就當我們的全部未來就靠它了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}let's just say our whole future hangs in the balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.57,0:07:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,葉綠體利用陽光將水分子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This chloroplast is using sunlight to break water molecules
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.54,0:07:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,分解成氫原子和氧原子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into atoms of hydrogen and oxygen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.04,0:07:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,將氫氣與二氧化碳結合產生糖\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It combines the hydrogen with carbon dioxide to make sugar,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.05,0:07:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,將氧氣作為廢氣排出\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and releases the oxygen as a waste product.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.38,0:07:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,要一探究竟 我們還要潛的更深\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}To see how it happens, we have to go even deeper,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.25,0:07:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,變得更小\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}get even smaller.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.89,0:07:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,小到原子級別\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We're talking atomic scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.16,0:07:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,成功了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Bingo.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.83,0:08:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,這條流水線是分子工業基地的核心\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This assembly line is the heartof the molecular industrial complex.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.23,0:08:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,在分子這個級別\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14\c&HFFFFFF&}At the molecular level,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.23,0:08:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,速度快到我們看不到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}things happen too fast for us to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.26,0:08:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我們必須讓它們慢下來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So we'll have to slow them down
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.67,0:08:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,放慢十億倍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}about a billion times.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.00,0:08:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,那些大分子就是二氧化碳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Those larger molecules are carbon dioxide.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.84,0:08:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,每一個分子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Each one of them is made
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.34,0:08:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,由1個碳原子和2個氧原子組成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of one carbon and two oxygen atoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.24,0:08:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,當陽光照射葉綠素的分子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When sunlight strikes a green molecule of chlorophyll,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.45,0:08:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,就會產生一系列的化學反應\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it sets in motion a series of chemical reactions,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.62,0:08:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,分解水分子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}breaking apart water molecules
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.45,0:08:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,釋放活潑的電子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and freeing energetic electrons.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.49,0:08:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,這只是日班的活\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And that's just the day shift,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.16,0:08:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,只在日光注入能量時工作\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when sunlight supplies the incoming stream of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.03,0:08:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,還有一組不分晝夜的工作\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's a second shift that works day and night
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.00,0:08:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,利用預留的太陽能工作\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}using the solar energy kept in reserve.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.50,0:08:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,自由電子的能量開始工作了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The energy of the free electrons is put to work,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.10,0:08:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,將二氧化碳與水中的氫結合\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}combining carbon dioxide with hydrogen from the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.31,0:08:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,產生糖  用以儲存太陽能\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The end product is sugar,which stores the solar energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.01,0:08:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,葉綠體從事太陽能採集工作\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The chloroplast is a three-billion-year-old
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.98,0:09:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,長達30億年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}solar energy collector.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.52,0:09:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,微觀世界的太陽能電池\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This sub-microscopic solar battery
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.29,0:09:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,驅動了所有的森林 田地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is what drives all the forests and the fields
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.82,0:09:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,甚至是海中的浮游生物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the plankton of the seas.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.06,0:09:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,還有動物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And the animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.79,0:09:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,包括我們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Including us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.86,0:09:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽能的生物圈\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The solar-powered biosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.20,0:09:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,比我們整個人類文明收集並處理的能量多出6倍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}collects and processes six times more power than our entire civilization
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.74,0:09:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,我們瞭解化學層面的光合作用工作原理\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We understand on a chemical level how photosynthesis works.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.37,0:09:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我們可以在實驗室複製這樣的過程\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We can recreate the process in a laboratory.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.51,0:09:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,但是我們做不到植物這麼好\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But we're not as good at it as plants are.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.31,0:09:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,這並不奇怪\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And it's not surprising,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.38,0:09:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,因為大自然已經這樣工作幾十億年了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}considering nature has been at this for billions of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.81,0:09:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,而我們才剛開始\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and we've only just started.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.92,0:09:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我們可以知道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But if we could figure out
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.48,0:09:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,光合作用的商業機密\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the trade secrets of photosynthesis,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.75,0:09:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,如今我們賴以生存的其他形式的能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}every of other source of energy we depend on today...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.69,0:09:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,煤 石油 天然氣都可以淘汰了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}coal, oil, natural gas would become obsolete.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.76,0:09:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,光合作用是終極綠色能源\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Photosynthesis is the ultimate green power.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.43,0:09:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,它不會污染大氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It doesn't pollute the air
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.33,0:09:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,事實上 碳中和人造光合作用可以很大程度上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and is, in fact, carbon neutral. Artificial photosynthesis on a big enough scale
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.70,0:10:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,減少溫室效應\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}could reduce the greenhouse effect
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.74,0:10:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,所帶來的氣候變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that's driving climate change in a dangerous direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.91,0:10:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,這裏開始蒸發了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Uh-oh, place is evaporating.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.45,0:10:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,該撤了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Time to get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.52,0:10:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,露珠的生命一閃即逝\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How fleeting is the life of a dewdrop.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.02,0:10:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,它在寒冷的夜裏從稀薄的空氣中凝結而成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It condenses from thin air in the cool of the night,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.22,0:10:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,卻在日出之後無影無蹤\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}only to vanish with the heat of the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.39,0:10:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,它的居民怎麼辦 水熊蟲呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And what of its inhabitants, the tardigrades?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.29,0:10:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,它們不會有事的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.03,0:10:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,因為它們可以幾年不喝水\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They can go without water for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.53,0:10:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,很難想像\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's hard to imagine,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.43,0:10:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,覆蓋地球表面的植物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but plants covered the surface of the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.10,0:10:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,幾億年後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for hundreds of millions of years
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.90,0:10:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,才開出第一朵花\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}before they put forth their first flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.37,0:10:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,大約1億年前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That was about a hundred million years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.28,0:10:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,恐龍滅絕前不久\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}shortly before the dinosaurs were wiped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.95,0:10:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,當時世界的顏色一定很單調\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our world must've been a relatively drab-looking place back then,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.12,0:10:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,只有綠色和褐色\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}dominated by shades of green and brown.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.39,0:10:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,是的那時是有大樹和蕨類 還有其他的植物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Yeah, there were giant trees and ferns and other plant life,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.72,0:10:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,但是沒有紫色的鳶尾花\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but not the purple of an iris
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.99,0:11:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,也沒有紅色的玫瑰花\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}or the crimson of a red, red rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.50,0:11:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,蘭花是最早出現的花之一\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Orchids were among the first flowering species
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.57,0:11:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,現在它們有著最多的品種\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to appear on earth, and they're the most diverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.18,0:11:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,達爾文特別癡迷馬達加斯加的彗星蘭\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Darwin was particularly fascinated by the comet orchid of Madagascar,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.32,0:11:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,這種花的花粉藏在一條又長又細的花徑底部\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a flower whose pollen is hidden at the bottom of a very long, thin spur.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.29,0:11:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,預測能力是驗證一種理論的最好方法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There can be no stronger test of an idea \than its predictive power.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.19,0:11:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,根據他的物競天擇的進化論基礎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}On the basis of his theory of evolution through natural selection
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.36,0:11:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,達爾文推測\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Darwin speculated that somewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.03,0:11:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,在馬達加斯加島上 一定有一種會飛的昆蟲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on the island of Madagascar, there must live flying insects
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.84,0:11:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,長著非常長的舌頭\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with extraordinarily lengthy tongues,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.97,0:11:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,長的足夠接觸到那些花粉\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}ones long enough to reach the pollen.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.84,0:11:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,從沒人看過這種動物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No one had ever seen such a beast there,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.45,0:11:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,但是達爾文堅信\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but Darwin insisted
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.18,0:11:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,肯定有這樣的動物存在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that an animal fitting this description must exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.52,0:11:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,當時相信他的人不多\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Few people at the time believed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.29,0:12:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,直到50多年後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It wasn't until more than 50 years later
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.82,0:12:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,才證明了達爾文的猜測是正確的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that Darwin was proven right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.16,0:12:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,1903年 有一種被稱為馬島長喙天蛾的蛾子在馬達加斯加被發現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In 1903, a huge hawk moth, called the Morgan's sphinx was discovered in Madagascar.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.36,0:12:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,受到彗星蘭花粉香味的吸引\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Attracted by the Comet Orchid's scent,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.90,0:12:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,這蛾子用它1英尺長的口器吸食花粉\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the moth slurps its pollen with its foot-long tongue,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.24,0:12:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,和達爾文猜測的一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}exactly as Darwin expected it would.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.41,0:12:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,更令人驚奇的是 發現這種蛾子時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's even more amazing that the Morgan's sphinx was discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.72,0:12:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,馬達加斯加島上超過90%的雨林已經遭到破壞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when you consider that more than 90% of Madagascar's rain forest had been destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.59,0:12:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,在達爾文著名的猜測多年後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In the years since Darwin's famous prediction,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.36,0:12:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,這種蛾子很有可能已經滅絕\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}this moth species could have easily become extinct
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.56,0:12:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,就和其他同類一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with all the others...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.36,0:12:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,它們每一個都是生命詩篇中的獨特樂章\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}every one of them a unique phrase of life's poetry,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.60,0:12:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,由萬古的進化寫在原子中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}written in the atoms by eons of evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.73,0:12:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,丁香花的芬芳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Ah, the fragrance of lilacs.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.93,0:13:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,這種香味\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's one of those scents
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.70,0:13:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,讓人不禁浮想翩翩\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that triggers a whole constellation of associations,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.77,0:13:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,很久前的每個夏天都是如此\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}all those junes of long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.91,0:13:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,怎會如此\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But how does that happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.71,0:13:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,味道是怎麼會讓你的頭腦中出現影像的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How does a smell prompt a movie to start running in your head?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.11,0:13:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,那不是我們能看到的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's not something we can see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.12,0:13:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,有可能是象光一樣的能量波嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Could it be a wave of energy, like light?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.42,0:13:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,還是一種微觀粒子呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Or is it some kind of microscopic particle?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.89,0:13:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,其實它是一種分子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's actually a molecule.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.59,0:13:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,每種味道 不論是來自烤焦的麵包\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Every odor we can sense, whether it comes from burnt toast
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.39,0:13:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,還是汽油 或者一片丁香花\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}gasoline, or a field of lilacs,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.90,0:13:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,都是一大片的分子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is a cloud of molecules.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.13,0:13:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,這些分子有種特定的形狀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}These molecules have particular shapes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.94,0:13:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,當我吸入它們時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When I inhale them,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.91,0:13:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,它們刺激我鼻子中一組特定的感受細胞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they stimulate a particular set of receptor cells in my nose.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.91,0:13:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,一種電子信號傳遞到我的大腦\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}An electrical signal then travels to my brain,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.15,0:13:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,告訴我這個味道是丁香花的香味\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which identifies the scent as lilac.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.12,0:13:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,不同的分子攜帶不同的味道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Other scents are carried by different molecules
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.25,0:13:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,它們的形狀也各異\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with different shapes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.92,0:13:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,但當我聞到一朵花 或者篝火\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But when I smell a flower or the smoke from a campfire
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.23,0:14:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,或者機器的潤滑油\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}or the grease from a motor gear,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.96,0:14:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,通常是涌現出大量的記憶\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I'm often flooded with memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.07,0:14:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,為什麼花香這麼簡單的東西能夠引起強烈的記憶呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Why is it that a simple thing such as the scent of a flower can trigger powerful memories?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.44,0:14:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,一定和我們的大腦進化方式有關\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It has to do with the way our brains have evolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.94,0:14:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,當大腦中的嗅神經受到刺激\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our sense of smell kicks in
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.31,0:14:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的嗅覺開始工作\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when the olfactory nerve in our brain is stimulated.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.68,0:14:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,這種神經就在扁桃體旁邊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That nerve is located very close to the amygdala,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.05,0:14:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,是我們情感體驗的組成部分\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a structure that is integral to our experience of emotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.99,0:14:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,也很靠近海馬體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's also very close to the Hippocampus,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.26,0:14:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,產生記憶的地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which helps us form memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.87,0:14:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,神經網絡將氣味信號\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The network of neurons that carry the scent signal
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.20,0:14:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,從我的鼻子傳遞到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from my nose to my brain has been fine-tuned
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.04,0:14:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我這經過上億年進化的大腦\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}over hundreds of millions of years of evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.21,0:14:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,這是一種生存機制 給我們發出警告\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's a survival mechanism that can alert us
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.51,0:14:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,讓我們避開危險\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to danger or guide us to safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.95,0:15:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你能提前發覺獵食者\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If you you can detect the predator
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.99,0:15:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,在他發動攻擊前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}before he's near enough to strike,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.02,0:15:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,或者在被大火困在森林前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}or the fire before it traps you in the forest,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.36,0:15:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,就會大大增加你的生存幾率\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}you have a much better chance to survive
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.53,0:15:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,然後把你的基因傳給下一代\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and pass on your genes to the next generation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.14,0:15:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,花田里的迷人芬芳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That lovely scent from this field of flowers
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.71,0:15:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,發出一組獨特的神經信號密碼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}sets off a unique combination of nerve signals.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.74,0:15:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,只有這個密碼可以打開我們大腦中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Only that exact combination can crack the safe
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.34,0:15:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,儲存關於丁香花的記憶保險箱\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}where the memory of lilacs is stored inside my brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.82,0:15:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,啥味道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Wonder who they're for.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.82,0:15:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,我們或許以後會知道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Maybe we'll find out later.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.89,0:15:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,但還有一個隱藏著的宇宙在等著我們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But first, there's another hidden cosmos waiting for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.04,0:16:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,植物們靜靜的呼吸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The plants are softly breathing,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.47,0:16:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,吸入二氧化碳分子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}inhaling molecules of carbon dioxide
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.37,0:16:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,呼出氧氣分子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and exhaling molecules of oxygen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.11,0:16:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,和我相反\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And I'm doing the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.61,0:16:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,與雪花和指紋不一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Unlike snowflakes and fingerprints,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.98,0:16:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,同類的原子或分子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}atoms or molecules of the same kind
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.78,0:16:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,都是完全的相同\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are utterly identical to one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.92,0:16:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,每次吸氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}With every breath we take,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.62,0:16:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,我們吸入的分子數量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we inhale as many molecules as there are stars
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.82,0:16:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,和已知宇宙的所有星星數量一樣多\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in all the galaxies in the visible universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.39,0:16:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,呼出的氣體與空氣流通交換\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And every breath we exhale is circulated through the air,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.46,0:16:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,在大地上逐漸混合\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and mixed gradually across the continents,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.00,0:16:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,讓別人也可以呼吸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it becomes available for others to breathe.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.97,0:16:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,一起呼吸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Breathe with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.11,0:16:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,我們大致吸入了1億的分子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We all just inhaled about 100 million molecules
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.65,0:16:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,這些分子曾經被所有的前人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that once passed through the lungs of everyone
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.85,0:17:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,呼吸過\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}who ever lived before us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.92,0:17:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,想想看 這種原子的再生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Think of it... This kind of atomic reincarnation
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.12,0:17:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,將我們與遠古的祖先聯繫在一起\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is another link to our distant ancestors,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.43,0:17:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,包括那些最初帶領我們探索\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}including those who first launched us on our explorations
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.96,0:17:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,未知宇宙的人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the unseen universes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.13,0:17:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,這些宇宙就如同你我一樣真實\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}These universes are as real as you or me,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.60,0:17:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,就在我們的身邊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and they surround us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.31,0:17:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,曾經我們如夢初醒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There was a moment when we awakened
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.71,0:17:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,開始用嶄新的方法審視和思考\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to a new way of thinking and seeing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.35,0:17:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,那是大約2500年前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It happened about 2,500 years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.82,0:17:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,在希臘的小島上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on the Greek islands that lie
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.65,0:17:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,位於東方與西方文明之間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}between the empires of the east and west.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.95,0:17:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,商人 遊客 水手們自由的融合\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There, merchants, tourists and sailors freely mingled,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.06,0:17:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,交流各自關於偉人和神的傳說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}exchanging tales of great kings and gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.19,0:17:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,在愛奧尼亞有個叫米利都的城市 就是今天的土耳其\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In Ionian cities and towns like Miletus, in what is now Turkey,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.70,0:17:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,一些現代生活的最基本元素\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the most fundamental elements
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.90,0:17:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,在那裏出現了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the way we live now first appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.24,0:18:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,第一次對生活形式的重現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Here, for the first time, reenactments of aspects of life
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.54,0:18:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,由專業人士創作並演繹\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}created and executed by professionals
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.51,0:18:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,期待可以深深感動觀眾的內心\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with the expectation of touching something deep within the hearts of the audience,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.15,0:18:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,或者只是逗他們開心\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}or just making them laugh...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.05,0:18:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,誕生了第一場演出 戲劇還有喜劇\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The first plays, dramas and comedies, were performed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.72,0:18:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,還有一種極其嶄新的概念\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Here, also, was born a radical new idea:
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.60,0:18:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,民治政府\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Government by the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.56,0:18:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,從最初模糊的不完美的概念 到如今的民主\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The first inklings, imperfect then as now, of a democracy,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.83,0:18:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,普通民眾也可以擁有某些權力的觀念\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the notion that the ordinary citizen might possess certain rights
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.17,0:18:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,在那時 在這裏誕生萌芽\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}come to us from this time and place.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.64,0:18:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,但在我看來 這個古代世界帶給我們的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But in my view, the most revolutionary innovation of all
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.01,0:18:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,最革命性的創新觀念是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to come to us from this ancient world was the idea
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.85,0:18:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,自然事件並不是眾神給我們的懲罰或獎勵\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that natural events were neither punishment nor reward from capricious gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.89,0:18:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,大自然的規律不一定要用\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The workings of nature could be explained
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.09,0:18:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,超自然力量來解釋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}without invoking the supernatural.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.26,0:18:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,表達出這種觀念的第一人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The first person to express this thought
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.56,0:18:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,名叫 泰利斯\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was a man named Thales.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.56,0:18:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}希臘哲學家
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.80,0:19:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,當閃電或地震時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When the thunder clapped or the earth quaked,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.80,0:19:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,並不是因為我們的所作所為觸怒了嚴厲的眾神\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it was not because something you did had somehow displeased the very demanding gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.04,0:19:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,只是一種我們可以理解的自然過程的結果\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No, it was the result of natural processes that we were capable of understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.41,0:19:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,儘管沒有任何記錄他原話的書籍留存下來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Though none of the books he is said to have written survive,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.15,0:19:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,泰利斯的思想光芒依然照耀我們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Thales kindled a flame that still burns to this day:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.22,0:19:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙運行的井井有條的原因\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The very idea of cosmos out of chaos,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.29,0:19:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙由我們可以理解的自然法則控制的這種觀念\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a universe governed by the order of natural laws that we can actually figure out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.69,0:19:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,這種偉大的觀念在泰利斯的頭腦中萌芽\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is the epic adventure that began in the mind of Thales.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.43,0:19:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,僅僅在泰利斯身後100年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Only a century following Thales' death,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.80,0:19:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,又一個天才出現了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}another genius came along.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.40,0:19:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,他與眾不同的是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And he, more than any other,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.74,0:19:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,第一個發現了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was the first to discover the existence
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.97,0:19:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,我們周圍未知宇宙的存在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the hidden universes that surround us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.01,0:19:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,來自阿夫季拉的德謨克利特是為真正的科學家\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Democritus of Abdera was a true scientist,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.12,0:19:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,充滿探索宇宙激情的男人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a man with a passionate desire to know the cosmos
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.52,0:19:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,也很會享受\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and to have fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.32,0:19:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,他曾說 "沒有狂歡的生活\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is the man who once said, "a life without parties
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.66,0:20:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,...就像沒有盡頭的漫漫長路"\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}would be like an endless road without an end."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.09,0:20:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,這就樣嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You mean, that's it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.86,0:20:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,就這麼簡單嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's all there is?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.50,0:20:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,只是虛無中的一堆原子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Just a bunch of atoms in a void?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.10,0:20:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,然也\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.77,0:20:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,你想想看\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Well, think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.14,0:20:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,這個世界必然是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The world has to be made
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.94,0:20:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,由虛無中無數的不可見的微粒組成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of countless indivisible particles in a void.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.27,0:20:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,否則萬物就不會移動 生長 被分離或改變\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Otherwise, nothing could move or grow, be divided or changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.35,0:20:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,如果沒有原子和容納它們的空曠太空的話\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Without atoms and empty space for them to move in,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.78,0:20:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,這個世界會變得像鐵板一塊 死氣沉沉\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the world would be solid, static and dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.33,0:20:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,別傷心了 少年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}so don't be sad, my friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.77,0:20:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,想想那無盡的可能性吧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Just think of the infinite possibilities
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.27,0:20:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,由那些原子排列組合所帶來的可能性\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that arise from different arrangements of those atoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.98,0:20:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,向這杯的酒 還有酒中的原子們致敬\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Here's to the atoms in this cup and in this wine...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.62,0:20:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,還有它們帶來的歡樂\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And to the laughter they make possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.12,0:20:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}當時的酒杯都由泥土燒製而成
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.19,0:20:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,都是用顯微鏡才能看到的礦物微粒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are microscopic mineral grains,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.12,0:20:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,遍佈酒杯的泥土\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Dispersed through the Clay of the cup
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.36,0:21:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,晶體的一種\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}different kinds of crystals,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.03,0:21:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,每個都有與眾不同的原子結構\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}each with its own distinctive atomic architecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.63,0:21:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,礦物結構很精妙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Mineral structures are exquisite,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.13,0:21:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,但是它們的結構形式有限\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but they have a limited repertoire.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.14,0:21:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,一粒石英就是一個由3個相同原子組成的晶格集合體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A grain of quartz is a lattice of the same three atoms
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.41,0:21:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有變化 不斷重複\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}repeated, without variation, over and over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.15,0:21:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,即使是相對複雜的礦物晶格 比如黃寶石\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Even a relatively complex mineral lattice like topaz,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.85,0:21:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,由10個左右的原子組成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}composed of ten or so atoms,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.32,0:21:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,也只是相同的原子結構\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}can only repeat the identical atomic structure
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.99,0:21:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,不斷重複\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}again and again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.25,0:21:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,為了轉換到另一個維度
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.32,0:21:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,為了將它從不斷重複的晶格束縛中釋放\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to free it from the lattice prison of endless repetition,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.73,0:21:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,你需要一個可以從任何方向與其他原子相結合的原子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}you need an atom that can bond in all directions with other atoms like itself
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.83,0:21:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,它也要能與其他不同的原子相結合\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as well as with atoms of different kinds.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.17,0:21:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,看 碳原子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Behold the carbon atom...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.71,0:21:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,地球上生命不可缺少的元素\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the essential element for life on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.91,0:22:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,為什麼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.78,0:22:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,碳之所以特殊 是因為它可以一次與最多4種原子結合\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Carbon is special because it can bond with up to four other atoms at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.52,0:22:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,它可以與許多其他種類的原子結合\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It can connect with many different kinds of atoms,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.29,0:22:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,也包括其他碳原子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as well as other carbon atoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.29,0:22:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,它可以彎曲成環狀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It can curl into rings
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.96,0:22:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,也可以連成一條線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and string together into chains,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.19,0:22:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,組成遠比任何一種晶體都複雜的分子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}building molecules far more complex than any crystal.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.80,0:22:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,其它原子都沒有這種靈活性\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No other atom has the same flexibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.74,0:22:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,就算擁有類似化學屬性的原子也不行\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Even atoms that have similar chemical properties,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.21,0:22:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,比如 硅\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}like silicon,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.81,0:22:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,也無法像碳這樣組成豐富多樣的分子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}can't form the amazing variety of molecules built on carbon.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.98,0:22:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,這種碳基分子 我們稱為 蛋白質\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The carbon-based molecules we call proteins,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.55,0:22:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,組成生命的分子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the molecules of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.75,0:22:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,包含了成千上萬的原子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}contain literally hundreds of thousands of atoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.95,0:22:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,碳原子是世界上一切生物分子的支柱\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Carbon atoms are the backbone of the molecules that make every living thing on earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.16,0:22:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,包括我們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}including us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.66,0:22:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是岩石和生物的區別\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's the difference between rocks and living things.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.57,0:22:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,生命可以製造出大量的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Life can make enormous molecules
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.00,0:23:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,有著驚人體積和複雜性的分子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of stunning size and complexity,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.51,0:23:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,自由自在地隨機應變\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}freeing matter to improvise,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.64,0:23:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,進化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}evolve,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.67,0:23:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,甚至 愛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and even love.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.46,0:23:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,孩子的父親 您別擔心\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Take it easy, dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.53,0:23:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,他並沒有真的碰到的她\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He never actually touched her.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.97,0:23:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,日常生活中以原子這個層面上來說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In everyday life on our world, on the scale of atoms,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.74,0:23:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,物體絕對不會相互接觸到對方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}material objects never really touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.64,0:23:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,每個原子的中心都有一個原子核\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Each atom has a tiny nucleus at its center,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.08,0:24:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,被力線電子雲所包圍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}surrounded by an electron cloud of lines of force.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.48,0:24:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,當原子彼此接近時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}As the atoms approach each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.99,0:24:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,男孩的電子雲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the boy's electron clouds
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.95,0:24:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,推開女孩的電子雲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}push away the girl's.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.56,0:24:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,超過99.9%的原子物質都集中在它的原子核中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}More than 99.9% of the matter of any atom is concentrated in its nucleus.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.93,0:24:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,原子核被電子雲包圍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The nucleus is surrounded by an electron cloud
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.40,0:24:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,電子雲形成無形的力場\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which produces an invisible field of force,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.80,0:24:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,就像減震器\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and acts like a shock absorber.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.11,0:24:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,電子雲的結構決定了元素的本質\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The configuration of the electron cloud determines the nature of an element.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.78,0:24:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,以地球上物質的正常情況來說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In the ordinary course of things here on earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.45,0:24:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,原子核永遠不會彼此接觸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the nuclei never touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.35,0:24:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我們有接觸的感覺\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We have a sensation of touching,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.45,0:24:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,那只不過是看不見的力場\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but that's really just our invisible force fields
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.09,0:24:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,相互重疊的同時相互排斥\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}overlapping and repelling each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.80,0:24:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,相較於原子的其他部分 原子核非常小\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The nucleus is very small compared to the rest of the atom.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.94,0:25:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,如果原子像這個教堂這麼大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If an atom were the size of this cathedral,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.98,0:25:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,原子核的尺寸也就是那粒灰塵的大小\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}its nucleus would be the size of that mote of dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.99,0:25:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,原子的大部分是空曠的空間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}An atom is mostly empty space.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.22,0:25:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,為了理解事物的本質\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}To understand the nature of matter,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.96,0:25:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,我們要去更深的地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we have to go deeper still,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.96,0:25:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,去一個比原子還小10萬倍的地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to a place 100,000 times smaller than the atom:
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.00,0:25:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,那就是它的原子核\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Its nucleus.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.17,0:25:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙中最簡單 但又最豐富的原子是氫原子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The simplest and most plentiful atom in the cosmos is hydrogen.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.64,0:25:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,它的原子核只有一個質子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Its nucleus is a single proton,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.88,0:25:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,所以它在元素週期表中位於第一位\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which makes hydrogen element number one.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.91,0:25:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,圍繞著它的雲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The clouds that surround it
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.75,0:25:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,是它唯一的電子可以運行的範圍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are the realms where the atom's lone electron is permitted to roam.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.72,0:25:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,原子核有兩個質子時會是什麼情況\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What happens when you have a nucleus with two protons?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.99,0:25:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,質子相互排斥\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Protons repel each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.66,0:25:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,為了讓它們保持在原子核內\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In order to hold them together in a nucleus,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.02,0:25:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,你還需要另一種粒子 稱之 中子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}you need other particles called neutrons.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.23,0:25:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,它們的工作是防止質子出軌\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Their job is to keep the protons from getting out of line.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.27,0:26:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,它們用強大的核引力壓制質子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They overwhelm the protons
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.27,0:26:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,原子核有2個質子的元素排名第2\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A nucleus with two protons is element number two,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.54,0:26:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,名曰 氦\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}otherwise known as helium.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.21,0:26:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,原子核有6個質子的元素排名第6\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A nucleus with six protons is element number six,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.25,0:26:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,就是碳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which is carbon,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.21,0:26:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,生命的基石\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the fundamental building block of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.35,0:26:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,金元素的原子核有79個質子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The nucleus of a gold atom has 79 protons.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.52,0:26:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,在周圍的雲中 它們吸引了79個電子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They attract 79 electrons in clouds around it
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.39,0:26:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,光與這些電子的互動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The way light interacts with those electrons
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.69,0:26:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,就是黃金閃光的原因\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is what makes gold glitter.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.29,0:26:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,原子核中每增加一個質子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Every additional proton in the nucleus
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.26,0:26:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,都需要有足夠的中子把它們聚集在一起\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}requires enough neutrons to bind them together...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.56,0:26:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,在一定程度上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Up to a point.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.23,0:26:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,你能塞進原子核的中子數量是有上限的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's an upper limit to the number of neutrons you can stuff into a nucleus
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.20,0:26:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,否則會變得不穩定\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}before it becomes unstable.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.97,0:26:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,有個地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I know a place
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.14,0:26:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,不同原子的原子核\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}where the nuclei of different atoms
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.21,0:26:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,能夠相互接觸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}actually do touch each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.26,0:27:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽看上去像個實體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The sun looks like a solid object,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.77,0:27:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,但並不是這樣的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but it's not.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.97,0:27:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,它把所有的原子都加熱到了氣態\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's so hot that all its atoms are always in their gaseous state.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.81,0:27:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,地球上將原子束縛產生液態和固體的粘合力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The bonds that join atoms to make solids and liquids on earth
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.01,0:27:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,不足以承受熾熱太陽的熱量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are not strong enough to withstand the heat of the broiling sun
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.88,0:27:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,那些耀眼氣體的弧形氣流使地球看上去渺小\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Those arcing streams of incandescent gas that dwarf the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.95,0:27:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,其實它們都受到太陽表面之下發射出來的力場的磁力線引導\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are guided by magnetic lines of force that emanate from below the surface of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.16,0:27:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽怎麼會這麼熱\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Why is the sun so hot?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.69,0:27:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,因為它驚人的引力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Because its own stupendous gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.00,0:27:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,將原子們積壓在一起\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is squeezing its atoms together.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.80,0:27:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,引力的能量轉換成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The energy of gravity is being transformed
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.44,0:27:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,移動原子的能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into the energy of moving atoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.57,0:27:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,那就是熱的來源\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's what heat is.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.27,0:27:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,越到太陽的內部\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The deeper we go into the sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.14,0:27:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,擠壓的力量越大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the greater the squeezing
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.94,0:27:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,溫度也越高\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the higher the temperature.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.21,0:28:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,在太陽的中心\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In the heart of the sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.78,0:28:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,原子的移動速度快到 它們碰撞時發生融化 原子核發生接觸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the atoms are moving so fast that when they collide, they fuse. Their nuclei touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.62,0:28:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽就是核聚變反應堆\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The sun is a nuclear fusion reactor,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.06,0:28:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,由它的引力來維繫\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}held together by its own gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.33,0:28:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,它在向內拉的引力和向外推的熱浪間取得平衡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's balanced between the inward pull of gravity and the outward push of its hot gases.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.24,0:28:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,這種平衡持續幾十億年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That balance has lasted billions of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.57,0:28:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,提供了使地球上生物進化成為可能的穩定性\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}providing stability that made possible the evolution of life on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.08,0:28:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,在太陽的核心 氫融合後變成氦\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In the sun's core, the fusion of hydrogen into helium
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.41,0:28:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,以光子的形式釋放核能\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}releases nuclear energy in the form of photons.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.58,0:28:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,這些光的微粒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}These particles of light
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.25,0:28:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,慢慢的來到表面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}slowly work their way to the surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.19,0:28:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,就是我們所見的日光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}where they're seen as sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.92,0:28:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,氦原子就是太陽核反應的殘渣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Helium is the ash of the sun's nuclear furnace.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.83,0:28:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽是一顆中等尺寸的恆星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The sun is a medium-sized star.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.70,0:28:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,它的核心溫度只不過1千萬度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Its core is only a lukewarm ten million degrees...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.33,0:28:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,只夠融化氫原子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}hot enough to fuse hydrogen,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.67,0:28:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,卻不足以融化氦原子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but too cold to fuse helium.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.67,0:29:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,銀河系中有很多恆星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There are many stars in the galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.07,0:29:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,比太陽熱得多\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that get much hotter,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.67,0:29:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,因為它們質量更大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}because they're more massive
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.21,0:29:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,引力更大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and have more gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.78,0:29:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,這些恆星將氦融化成更重的元素 比如 碳和氧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Such stars fuse helium into heavier elements, like carbon and oxygen.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.91,0:29:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,等它們老了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In their old age,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.85,0:29:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,它們慢慢的將這些元素散播到太空中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they gently diffuse these elements into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.92,0:29:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,還有些恆星 質量更大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Other stars, more massive yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.12,0:29:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,一生苦短 英年早逝\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}live fast and die young
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.43,0:29:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,卒於災難性的超新星大爆炸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in cataclysmic supernova explosions.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.43,0:29:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的銀河系中 每一百年 這樣的恆星就會變成超新星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In our galaxy, such stars go supernova about once a century.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.68,0:29:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,這些爆炸比太陽核心熱的多得多\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Those explosions are far hotter than the core of the sun
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.77,0:29:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,熱的足夠把鐵元素變成更重的元素\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}hot enough to transform elements like iron into all the heavier ones
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.07,0:29:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,並把它們噴向太空\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and spew them into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.28,0:29:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,大麥哲倫星雲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The large magellanic cloud
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.18,0:29:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,使我們銀河系的鄰居\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is a neighboring galaxy of our milky way.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.38,0:29:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,可以在南半球的星空中看到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's visible in the skies of the Southern hemisphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.12,0:29:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,當超新星爆炸時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When a supernova explodes,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.72,0:29:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,它的亮度超過它的整個星系\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}its brightness rivals that of its entire galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.84,0:30:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,但這些光也只是爆炸產生的能量中的大約1%\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But all that light is only about one percent of the energy liberated in the explosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.67,0:30:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,其它的能量化成宇宙中最常見\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The rest of the energy is carried off by the most common
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.78,0:30:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,也最神秘的微粒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the most mysterious particles in the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.11,0:30:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,現在就有幾萬億的這種微粒穿過你的身體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There are trillions of them passing through you right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.52,0:30:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,然而即使為了找到一個這樣的微粒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and yet tracking down even one of them
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.05,0:30:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,也需要我們去到地球上最離奇的地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}will take us to one of the strangest places on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.91,0:30:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,追蹤野生的中微子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Stalking the wild neutrino
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.01,0:30:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,是最小眾的運動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is the rarest of sport.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.84,0:30:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,追蹤它們的難度 難得令人驚訝\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The lengths one must go to track them down is nothing short of astonishing
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.18,0:30:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,歡迎來到超級神岡探測器\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Welcome to Super Kamiokande,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.85,0:30:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,日本地下中微子探測器的內部\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the subterranean Japanese neutrino detection chamber.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.69,0:30:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我們身處地表之下超過半英里\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We're more than a half mile beneath earth's surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.69,0:30:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}也就是大約1公里
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.86,0:30:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,你或許會問 哪個正常人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You might ask, "well, who in their right mind
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.13,0:31:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,會把天文台埋在這麼深的地下\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}would bury an astronomical observatory so far underground?"
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.36,0:31:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,這些人狩獵宇宙中最神出鬼沒的獵物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Those who hunt the most elusive prey in the cosmos:
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.93,0:31:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,中微子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The neutrino.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.93,0:31:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,這個龐大的光探測器陣列\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This enormous array of light detectors
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.94,0:31:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,圍繞著5萬噸蒸餾水\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}surrounding 50,000 tons of distilled water
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.01,0:31:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,設計這個陷阱只為了抓捕中微子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is a trap designed to catch neutrinos only.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.51,0:31:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,其他粒子 例如宇宙射線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Other particles, such as cosmic rays...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.94,0:31:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,大部分是從太空中落下的質子和電子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}mostly protons and electrons that rain down from space...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.95,0:31:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,無法穿過我們頭頂的岩石\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}cannot get through all that rock above us.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.55,0:31:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,但這些對中微子來說都不是障礙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But matter poses no obstacle to a neutrino.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.95,0:31:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,中微子可以穿過100光年厚的鐵板\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A neutrino could pass through 100 light-years of steel
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.99,0:31:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,甚至不會減速\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}without even slowing down.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.46,0:31:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,中微子幾乎不受其他物質影響\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Neutrinos hardly interact with matter at all
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.20,0:31:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是為什麼我們需要如此大費周章\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's why you need so much of it to catch even one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.50,0:31:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,在很罕見的情況下\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}On those rare occasions when a neutrino
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.57,0:31:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,中微子和其他微粒發生衝突\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}actually does collide with a particle of ordinary matter,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.34,0:31:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,它會產生一個幽靈般的環形閃光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it produces a ghostly, ring-shaped flash of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.54,0:31:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,我們守株待兔\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We're lying in wait
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.24,0:31:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,等一個幾乎沒有重量的微粒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for a particle that weighs next to nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.85,0:31:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,甚至比電子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Even the miniscule electron
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.85,0:31:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,還輕100萬倍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}has more than a million times its mass...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.85,0:32:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,那裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.55,0:32:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,1987年 當大麥哲倫星雲的超新星爆炸時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When the supernova in the large magellanic cloud blew its top in 1987
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.06,0:32:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是當時這裏出現的景象\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}this is what it would have looked like in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.99,0:32:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,請記住 大麥哲倫星雲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Now remember, the large magellanic cloud
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.43,0:32:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,在我們的南半球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is in our Southern hemisphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.76,0:32:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,所以這些中微子不是穿過\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}so the neutrinos didn't come through
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.37,0:32:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,我們頭頂上半英里的岩石\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that half-mile of rock above us,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.00,0:32:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,而是必須穿過我們身下\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they had to pass through the thousands of miles
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.60,0:32:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,幾千英里的岩石和鐵才能到達這裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of rock and iron below us to reach this detector.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.44,0:32:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,但是最酷的事情是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But the coolest thing was that those neutrinos
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.11,0:32:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,中微子比超新星發出的光早3小時到達地球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}hit earth three hours before the light from the supernova did.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.78,0:32:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,如果沒有什麼能比光跑得快\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If nothing can travel faster than light,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.02,0:32:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,這又是怎麼回事呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}how could that possibly be?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.02,0:32:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,星之將死\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is a dead star walking.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.93,0:32:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,看上去好像挺正常 但是在它的深處大災難已經發生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It may look normal, but deep within it something cataclysmic is happening
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.90,0:32:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,這顆藍色的超級巨大的恆星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This blue super giant star
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.27,0:32:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,內部即將發生爆炸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}has already begun to explode inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.31,0:33:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,如同即將沉船上的老鼠 慌不擇路\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Like rats deserting a sinking ship, the neutrinos
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.91,0:33:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,即將爆炸的恆星內部產生的中微子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}produced in the heart of the exploding star
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.41,0:33:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,以接近光速的速度向外逃逸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}race outward at near the speed of light,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.98,0:33:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,幾秒內穿過覆蓋物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}through overlying mass in only a few seconds
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.99,0:33:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,但是爆炸氣體的衝擊波\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But the shock wave of the exploding gas
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.22,0:33:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,從恆星內部緩緩踱出\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}plods along from the center of the star
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.26,0:33:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,只有光速的萬分之一\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}at 1/10,000 the speed of light
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.89,0:33:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,直到最後抵達\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}until it finally reaches
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.13,0:33:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,恆星的表面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the star's surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.60,0:33:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,變成了1987年的超新星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}turning it into supernova 1987a.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.44,0:33:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,要好幾個小時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It took hours for the explosion
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.14,0:33:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,爆炸才能到達表面 然後向外噴發\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to reach the surface of the star and blow it wide open,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.75,0:33:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,將極度炙熱的內核炸開\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}exposing the super hot core.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.88,0:33:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,中微子已經贏在了起跑線上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The neutrinos had an insurmountable head start.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.65,0:33:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是為什麼閃光會比中微子晚這麼多到達地球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's why the flash of light arrived on earth so much later than the shower of neutrinos.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.49,0:33:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,在「野生」中微子被捕獲前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Before anyone had ever snared the wild neutrino,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.96,0:33:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,它已經存在於理論物理學家的腦海中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it existed in the mind of a theoretical physicist.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.86,0:33:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,就如同查爾斯·達爾文知道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Just as Charles Darwin knew
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.93,0:34:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,必定有一種超級長鼻生物生活在馬達加斯加\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}there must be an extremely long-nosed creature flying around somewhere in Madagascar
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.54,0:34:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,一位名叫沃爾夫岡·泡利的20世紀物理學家\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a 20th-century physicist named Wolfgang Pauli...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.38,0:34:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,致力於尋找一種微粒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was desperately seeking a particle
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.35,0:34:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,用來拯救現代物理學的支柱之一\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to rescue one of the pillars of modern physics,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.65,0:34:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,能量守恆定律\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the law of the conservation of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.83,0:34:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我為什麼沒有退縮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So why didn't I flinch?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.89,0:34:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,因為科學定律與其它人類活動的根本區別\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Because the laws of science differ fundamentally from those of other human endeavors
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.03,0:34:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,要將一種設想變成科學定律\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In order for an idea to become a scientific law,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.57,0:34:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,必須要無懈可擊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it has to unbreakable.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.40,0:34:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是為何我願意賭上我的臉\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's why I was willing to bet this face
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.17,0:34:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,來證明能量守恆定律\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on the laws of conservation of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.08,0:34:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你在家自己嘗試\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Now, if you try this at home,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.51,0:34:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,千萬小心不要推這個球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}take care not to give the cannonball a push.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.51,0:34:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,那會增加能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's adding energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.15,0:34:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,這球肯定會回來造成傷害\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the ball will surely come back and do some damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.72,0:34:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,只要像這樣輕輕放手\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You just have to let it go, like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.92,0:34:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,抬起這個球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}By lifting the ball,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.26,0:34:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,你給它勢能\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}you give it gravitational energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.99,0:35:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,使它可能墜落並且加速\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which is the potential to fall and accelerate.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.99,0:35:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,球在弧度底部時速度達到最大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The cannonball is going fastest when it's at the bottom of its arc
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.23,0:35:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,在那個時候\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and at that moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.90,0:35:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,它把所有的勢能轉化成動能\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it's converted all of its gravitational energy to the energy of motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.17,0:35:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,搖擺時 球不斷轉換能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}As it swings, the cannonball is constantly exchanging
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.87,0:35:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,從一種轉換到另一種\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}one of these two kinds of energy for the other,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.11,0:35:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,但是能量的總量保持不變\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but the total amount of energy remains constant.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.34,0:35:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是能量守恆定律的例子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's an example of the law of conservation of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.71,0:35:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,放開球的那刻\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Once the cannonball is released,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.18,0:35:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,它就無法獲得更多的能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it can never gain more energy than it had to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.25,0:35:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,它不可能飛過來打到我的鼻子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It has no way to fly up and break my nose.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.59,0:35:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,能量這筆賬永遠是平衡的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The energy accounting books are always strictly balanced.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.59,0:35:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,做不得假\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's no such thing as cheating.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.96,0:35:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,在20世紀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So in the 20th century,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.80,0:35:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,當科學家首次精確測量出原子的能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when physicists first calculated the energy of atoms precisely,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.20,0:35:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,他們驚訝的發現了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they were startled to discover
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.47,0:35:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,違背這個定律的情況\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}an apparent violation of this law.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.07,0:35:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,他們發現在一些放射性原子中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They found that in some radioactive atoms,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.58,0:35:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,原子核自發的噴出一個電子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the nucleus can spontaneously eject an electron.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.98,0:35:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,將原子轉變成另一種元素\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This transforms the atom into a different element.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.55,0:36:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,物理學家迷惑了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The physicists were mystified.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.12,0:36:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,逃逸電子的能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The energy of the escaped electron
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.22,0:36:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,加上新元素的能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}plus that of the new element
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.22,0:36:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,少於原有原子核的能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}adds up to less than the energy in the original nucleus.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.56,0:36:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,定律指出\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But the law says,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.46,0:36:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,能量既不會憑空產生 也不會憑空消失\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}"thou shall not destroy or create energy."
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.40,0:36:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,那麼那些能量去了哪裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So where did the missing energy go?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.27,0:36:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,1930年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In 1930...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.44,0:36:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,沃爾夫岡·泡利預測\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Wolfgang Pauli predicted
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.00,0:36:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,一定有一種未知的微粒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}there must be an undiscovered particle,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.14,0:36:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,帶走了這些能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}one that makes off with the missing energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.61,0:36:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,當時 沃爾夫岡·泡利感嘆\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}At the time, Pauli lamented
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.41,0:36:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,如此微小的虛幻微粒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that such a phantom particle might be so minute,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.85,0:36:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,迅速而難以琢磨\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}swift and evasive
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.78,0:36:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,可能永遠都探測不到了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as to forever defy detection.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.85,0:36:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,好在那只是他罕有的一次錯誤預測\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But that was a rare failure of his imagination
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.29,0:36:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,因為科學家總是不斷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}because science is always searching
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.49,0:36:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,尋找探索的新方法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for a way to go deeper still.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.36,0:36:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,幾十年後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A generation later,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.30,0:36:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,在核反應堆的輻射中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Pauli's neutrinos were actually detected for the first time
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.66,0:36:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,中微子第一次被人們探測到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in radiation from a nuclear reactor.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.27,0:36:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,雖然很艱難 但從那之後我們不斷找到更多的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And we've been finding them, with difficulty, ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.20,0:36:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,如今 有些科學家們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There are scientists today
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.11,0:37:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,嘗試利用那些中微子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}who are trying to find a way to ride those neutrinos
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.38,0:37:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,來研究時間的起源\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}all the way back to the beginning of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.38,0:37:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,一起去看看他們的成就  那是一面永恆之牆\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We'll go as far as they have gone to come up against the wall of forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.65,0:37:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,永恆之牆並不新鮮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The wall of forever is nothing new.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.42,0:37:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的祖先也遇到過\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our ancestors came up against it
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.39,0:37:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,幾乎就在他們第一次開始想像時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}almost as soon as they first started imagining it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.53,0:37:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,幾千年前 公元前13世紀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A million dawns ago, in the 13th century bc,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.33,0:37:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,埃及人建造了阿布辛貝勒神廟\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the Egyptian built this temple at Abu Simbel
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.87,0:37:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,紀念法老王拉美西斯二世\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to honor the Pharaoh Ramses II,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.94,0:37:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,在這裏留下了四座巨大的石像\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}depicted here in four colossal statues.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.17,0:37:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,在這位偉大君主之上真正的王者其實是鷹首太陽神\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Reigning even above even this mighty king is the falcon-headed Ra-Harakhti
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.11,0:37:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽之神\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}God of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.79,0:38:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,這座神廟被設計成每年只有兩次\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The temple was designed so that the light from the rising sun
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.69,0:38:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,旭日的霞光金輝才會射入神殿\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}could only enter the sanctuary on two days every year.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.03,0:38:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,當光線照進神廟\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}As the rays enter the temple,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.06,0:38:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,在貫穿整個神殿前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they burnish the statues of the gods with their golden light
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.70,0:38:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,日光使眾神的石像閃耀著金色的光芒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}before penetrating the sanctuary.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.70,0:38:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,但是 仍有一位神的石像依然處在陰影中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Even then, one God remains in shadow.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.71,0:38:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,普塔 創造之神\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Ptah, lord of creation,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.21,0:38:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,彷彿暗示宇宙的起源注定永遠神秘\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as if the origin of the universe must forever be concealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.99,0:38:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,感受陽光照在臉上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Feel the sun on your face.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.82,0:38:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,使你溫暖的能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The energy that warms you
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.42,0:38:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,來自幾千萬年前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}began its journey some ten million years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.59,0:38:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽的核心\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the heart of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.73,0:38:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,與中微子不同\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Unlike neutrinos,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.80,0:38:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,質子需要\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the photons needed
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.63,0:38:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,這麼久的時間才能從核心到達表面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that long to work their way out from the core to the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.64,0:38:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,為什麼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.67,0:38:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,因為它們與太陽的原子每秒發生幾十億次的碰撞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Because they were colliding billions of times per second with the sun's atoms
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.01,0:38:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,每次撞擊都將它們推向不同的方向\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}every collision sending them off in a random direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.91,0:39:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,它們一旦到達表面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But once they finally reached the surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.91,0:39:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,它們就徹底解放 以光的速度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they were free to dash nonstop, at the speed of light
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.09,0:39:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,只用區區8分20秒 就來到你的面前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in a mere eight minutes and 20 seconds from the sun to you
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.82,0:39:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,一千萬歲高齡的陽光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Ten-million-year-old light on your face.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.33,0:39:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,當那光離開太陽核心時 又是怎麼的景象呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What was happening when that light left the heart of the sun?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.87,0:39:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙年歷將宇宙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The cosmic calendar compresses
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.94,0:39:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,整整138億年的歷史\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the entire 13.8 billion year history
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.78,0:39:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,壓縮到一年的時間內\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the universe into a single year.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.88,0:39:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,每個月代表10億年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Every month represents about a billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.45,0:39:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,一天就是4千萬年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Every day, about 40 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.35,0:39:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙的歷史如此悠久 在年歷上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The universe is so old that, on the cosmic calendar,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.62,0:39:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,1千萬年前 也只不過是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}ten million years ago only takes us back as far as...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.39,0:39:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,這一年的最後一天的下午6點\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}6:00 P.M. on the last evening of the last day of the year
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.90,0:39:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,那我們呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And what about us?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.50,0:39:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,人類還沒開始進化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Humans had yet to evolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.37,0:40:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,1千萬年前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Ten million years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.14,0:40:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的祖先還是類人猿\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}our ancestors were anthropoid apes,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.57,0:40:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,活躍在非洲的叢林中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}swinging through the trees of Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.51,0:40:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,對我們來說 1千萬年好像很久遠\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}To us, ten million years seems like a long time,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.01,0:40:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,但是對於宇宙來說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but it's only the length of an afternoon
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.42,0:40:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,那只不過是半天而已\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on the timescale of the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.22,0:40:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,45億年前 太陽開始放出光芒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The sun began fusing hydrogen 4,500 million years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.19,0:40:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙歷上的8月31號\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}August 31 on the cosmic calendar.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.93,0:40:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的銀河系\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our milky way galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.00,0:40:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,大約100億歲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is about 10,000 million years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.10,0:40:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,第一個星系比它還早幾十億年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The first galaxies formed about a few billion years earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.21,0:40:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,有東西阻擋我們回到更遠的過去\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Something keeps me from going any further back in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.18,0:40:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,是什麼呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.85,0:40:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,是光與時間的本質\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's the nature of light and time.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.75,0:40:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,因為光的速度有限\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Because light travels at a finite speed,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.95,0:40:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我們所看到的宇宙 其實只是過去的光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to look across space is to look back in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.86,0:41:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,看得越遠\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So the farther we see,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.03,0:41:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,看到的光越古老\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the older the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.87,0:41:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,這是我們所能看到宇宙歷史上最古老的光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is as far back in the history of the cosmos as we can see with light.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.70,0:41:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,這是宇宙剛誕生的樣子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's a baby picture of universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.14,0:41:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,只有38萬歲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when it was only 380,000 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.24,0:41:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙歷上最初的15分鐘\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's 15 minutes into January 1 on the cosmic calendar
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.91,0:41:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,我們用微波望遠鏡看向宇宙的盡頭\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If we look as far as we can see in any direction using microwave telescopes
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.09,0:41:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,看到的就是這樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}this is what we see,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.55,0:41:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,大爆炸留下的光暈\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the glow left over from the Big Bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.89,0:41:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,想像一下 可觀測宇宙的所有物質和能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Imagine that all the matter and energy of the observable universe
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.79,0:41:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,都被濃縮成這樣的大小\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was concentrated into something no larger than this
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.10,0:41:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是當時宇宙的大小\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's the size of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.00,0:41:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,當它只有一分之一萬億歲時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when it was a trillionth of a trillionth of a trillionth of a second old
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.41,0:41:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,幾千億個星系的物質與能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}All the matter and energy of the hundred billion galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.98,0:41:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,如今擴展到方圓幾十億光年的範圍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}now splayed out across the billions of light-years
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.08,0:41:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,曾經都被禁錮在這個彈珠大小的東西內\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}were once pent up in something the size of a marble
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.45,0:42:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,你能想像出那顆彈珠有多緊密嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Can you imagine how tightly packed that marble must have been?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.42,0:42:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,稠密得使任何光都無法穿過\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Far too dense for any kind of light to move through it,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.29,0:42:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,但這阻礙不了中微子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but no obstacle for the likes of neutrinos.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.09,0:42:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,大爆炸必定產生了數量驚人的中微子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The big bang must have produced stupendous numbers of neutrinos,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.00,0:42:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,它們順暢地穿過那些緊密得難以置信的物質\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which flew unhindered through that inconceivable crush of matter
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.70,0:42:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,使它們幾乎無法被探測的最關鍵因素是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The very thing that makes them almost impossible to detect
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.94,0:42:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,它們可以穿過遮掩時間起源的厚重幕布\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is what allows neutrinos to sail through the curtain that conceals the beginning of time
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.71,0:42:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,它們在哪裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Where are they now?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.31,0:42:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,在這裏 在那裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They are here, they're there,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.88,0:42:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙中無處不在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}everywhere throughout the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.12,0:42:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙誕生時中微子就在你的內心深處\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Neutrinos from creation are within you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.02,0:42:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,從一個彈珠\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}From a marble...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.29,0:42:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,到整個宇宙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}To the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.03,0:42:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,這是一條泰利斯和德謨克利特2500年前帶我們走上的路\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is the road that Thales and Democritus put us on some 2,500 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.17,0:42:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,無盡的探索之路\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a road of endless searching,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.24,0:43:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,不斷的有條不紊的探索新的世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a relentless, systematic hunt for new worlds
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.58,0:43:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,並且不斷加深對自然的理解\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and an ever-deepening understanding of nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.68,0:43:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,你們中有人會接過火炬 帶領我們走上一條更寬廣的大路嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Who among you will pick up that torch and take us down that next stretch of road?
